# Code Review Standards for JetBrains AI Assistant

## Code Quality Review
- Is the code clear and understandable?
- Does it follow the project's coding standards?
- Are there any code smells or anti-patterns?
- Is the code maintainable and extensible?

## Functionality Review
- Does the code fulfill the intended requirements?
- Are all edge cases handled properly?
- Are error conditions handled appropriately?
- Does the code behave as expected under load/usage?

## Performance Review
- Are there any performance bottlenecks?
- Is the code efficient in terms of time and space complexity?
- Are resources managed properly (memory, connections, etc.)?
- Are database queries optimized?

## Security Review
- Are inputs validated and sanitized?
- Are there any potential security vulnerabilities?
- Is sensitive data handled securely?
- Are authentication and authorization properly implemented?

## Testing Review
- Are there adequate unit tests covering the new functionality?
- Are edge cases and error conditions tested?
- Do tests follow the project's testing patterns?
- Do all tests pass consistently?

## Documentation Review
- Is the code adequately commented where necessary?
- Are public APIs documented?
- Are changes reflected in relevant documentation?
- Are any configuration changes documented?

## Architecture Review
- Does the code fit well within the existing architecture?
- Are the right design patterns being used?
- Is there appropriate separation of concerns?
- Are dependencies managed properly?

## Review Process Guidelines
- Be constructive and specific in feedback
- Focus on the code, not the person
- Suggest improvements rather than just pointing out problems
- Acknowledge good practices and elegant solutions
- Verify that all feedback has been addressed before approving